title: Royal Caribbean, Starbucks, Tyson Foods: Stocks That Defined the Week
sub_head: Here are seven major companies whose stocks moved on the week’s news
body:
Royal Caribbean Group
Stocks were bolstered this past week by hopes that the new Omicron strain of Covid-19 will have a less-pronounced impact on travel and consumer confidence than first feared. Scientists and vaccine makers are still assessing the severity of Omicron and how well existing vaccines may work against it, but Wall Street traders have increased conviction another major economic shock isn’t coming. Cruise lines were among the biggest winners, with Royal Caribbean Group jumping 8.2% Monday, and Carnival Corp. rising 8.1%.
